    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY (FS-6205/6305)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY (FS-6205/6305)</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>During disassembly, lay all parts on a clean bench in the order of removal to facilitate
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>The following steps correspond to the numbers in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302673">Figure 73</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302673" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302673" filename="../figg13/G1302673.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 73. Disassemble Mainshaft Assembly (FS-6205/6305)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the mainshaft front facing up, install the mainshaft assembly vertically in a vise.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 4th-5th speed synchronizer and cups.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a puller mounted behind 4th-5th clutch hub to remove the hub and bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 4th gear, bearings and spacer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove snap ring, thrust washer and locating ball.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 3rd gear, bearings and spacer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2nd-3rd speed synchronizer and cups.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove snap ring and 2nd-3rd shift hub.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2nd gear, bearings and spacer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove snap ring, thrust washer and locating ball.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st gear, bearings and spacer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st speed synchronizer.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>The following steps correspond to the numbers in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302674">Figure 74</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302674" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302674" filename="../figg13/G1302674.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 74. Disassemble Mainshaft Assembly (FS-6205/6305)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the mainshaft rear facing up, install the mainshaft assembly vertically in a vise.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a puller to remove reverse gear, washer and rear bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove reverse gear bearings and spacer.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
